---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Download your Section 75 Claim Pack"
  description="Thank you for purchasing the Section 75 Claim Pack. Your download is ready."
>
  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">

    <h1>Your claim pack is ready to download</h1>

    <p>
      Thank you for your purchase. The Section 75 Claim Pack is a single plain-English PDF workbook. Download it now and save it somewhere you can find it again — you may need it over the coming weeks as your claim progresses.
    </p>

    <div class="not-prose my-8">
      <a id="download-btn" href="#" class="btn-primary" aria-disabled="true">
        Preparing your download…
      </a>
      <p id="download-error" class="hidden mt-3 text-sm text-red-700">
        We could not verify your payment session. If you have just completed payment, please <a href="/contact/" class="underline">contact us</a> with your payment receipt and we will send the file directly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <script>
      const btn = document.getElementById('download-btn') as HTMLAnchorElement;
      const err = document.getElementById('download-error') as HTMLParagraphElement;
      const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
      const sessionId = params.get('session_id');

      if (sessionId && sessionId.startsWith('cs_')) {
        btn.href = `/api/download?session_id=${encodeURIComponent(sessionId)}`;
        btn.textContent = 'Download the claim pack (PDF)';
        btn.removeAttribute('aria-disabled');
      } else {
        btn.classList.add('hidden');
        err.classList.remove('hidden');
      }
    </script>

    <h2>What is in the workbook</h2>

    <p>The PDF is a guided workbook that walks you through your claim from start to finish. It contains:</p>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>A simple start-here guide</strong> — explains what Section 75 is, how the process works, and what to expect from your bank.</li>
      <li><strong>A 5-minute Section 75 checker</strong> — confirms your purchase qualifies before you write to your bank.</li>
      <li><strong>A one-page claim details worksheet</strong> — a structured form to pull together the key facts of your case.</li>
      <li><strong>An evidence checklist</strong> — tailored to the most common claim types, so you know what to gather and send.</li>
      <li><strong>An initial Section 75 claim letter</strong> — a formal letter citing Section 75(1) of the Consumer Credit Act 1974, covering non-delivery, faulty goods, goods not as described, and business failure.</li>
      <li><strong>A short chase message</strong> — a follow-up template if your bank does not respond within the required timeframe.</li>
      <li><strong>Rebuttal templates for common bank rejection reasons</strong> — responses covering the most frequent grounds banks use to reject valid claims.</li>
      <li><strong>A Financial Ombudsman complaint template</strong> — for use if the bank issues a final rejection or fails to respond within eight weeks.</li>
      <li><strong>A plain-English glossary and official sources</strong> — definitions of the terms your bank will use, and links to the primary legislation and FOS guidance.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>
      Placeholder text throughout — the details you need to fill in — is clearly marked so you cannot miss it.
    </p>

    <h2>Where to start</h2>

    <p>
      Start at the beginning. The start-here guide and the checker will confirm your purchase qualifies and point you to the right letter for your situation.
    </p>

    <p>
      If your bank has already rejected your claim, go directly to the rebuttal templates section and select the response that matches the reason they gave. If you are unsure which applies, the <a href="/guide/">complete Section 75 guide</a> covers the most common rejection grounds and the correct response to each.
    </p>

    <h2>Problems with the download?</h2>

    <p>
      If the file did not download or you cannot open it, <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> and we will help you access it. Please include the email address you used for payment.
    </p>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
